07. Return Statement
    //Program
        def cube(num):
            return num*num*num          //Without "return", it prints out none or null
            print("Hello")                        //All codes that are below the return keyword, it wont run (the return keyword breaks the function)
        result = cube(4)
        print(result)                             //Output: 64

